{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876614796,"sessionID":"ses_28581a9eeffeMoSglUwrTN7FTL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7ea4a9001RU3K2g8hcujNqY","messageID":"msg_d7a7e98c4001Zd3WZZMVqL1XBW","sessionID":"ses_28581a9eeffeMoSglUwrTN7FTL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a5dac2e5b0484216ac8d40ac390180a8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 Implementation Notes\n2: \n3: ## Implementation Status\n4: - [ ] Design document\n5: - [ ] API specification\n6: - [ ] Client implementation\n7: - [ ] Error handling\n8: - [ ] Tests\n9: - [ ] Documentation\n10: \n11: ## Implementation Details\n12: \n13: ### Files Created\n14: \n15: [To be filled during implementation]\n16: \n17: ### Test Coverage\n18: \n19: [To be filled during implementation]\n20: \n21: ### API Contract\n22: \n23: [To be filled during implementation]\n24: \n25: ### Notes\n26: \n27: [To be filled during implementation]\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 Implementation Notes\n\n## Implementation Status\n- [ ] Design document\n- [ ] API specification\n- [ ] Client implementation\n- [ ] Error handling\n- [ ] Tests\n- [ ] Documentation\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created\n\n[To be filled during implementation]\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n[To be filled during implementation]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/README.md","time":{"start":1775876614780,"end":1775876614795}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876614798,"sessionID":"ses_28581a9eeffeMoSglUwrTN7FTL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7ea7b1001yUQTmgxrxu1xD2","messageID":"msg_d7a7e98c4001Zd3WZZMVqL1XBW","sessionID":"ses_28581a9eeffeMoSglUwrTN7FTL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a8a473060698450f9c8d43b60ee35fbf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Specification\n2: \n3: ## Module: sdk-python\n4: \n5: ### CodeInterpreterClient Class\n6: \n7: #### Constructor\n8: \n9: ```python\n10: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n11:     def __init__(\n12:         self,\n13:         base_url: str,\n14:         api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n15:         timeout: int = 30,\n16:         max_retries: int = 3\n17:     ) -> None\n18: ```\n19: \n20: **Parameters:**\n21: - `base_url`: Base URL of the CodeInterpreter service\n22: - `api_key`: Optional API key for authentication\n23: - `timeout`: Request timeout in seconds (default: 30)\n24: - `max_retries`: Maximum number of retry attempts (default: 3)\n25: \n26: #### Session Management Methods\n27: \n28: ##### create_session\n29: \n30: ```python\n31: async def create_session(\n32:     self,\n33:     workspace_id: str,\n34:     timeout: int = 300,\n35:     metadata: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n36: ) -> Session\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Parameters:**\n40: - `workspace_id`: ID of the workspace\n41: - `timeout`: Session timeout in seconds (default: 300)\n42: - `metadata`: Optional metadata dictionary\n43: \n44: **Returns:** `Session` object\n45: \n46: **Raises:** `SessionCreationError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n47: \n48: ##### get_session\n49: \n50: ```python\n51: async def get_session(self, session_id: str) -> Session\n52: ```\n53: \n54: **Parameters:**\n55: - `session_id`: ID of the session\n56: \n57: **Returns:** `Session` object\n58: \n59: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n60: \n61: ##### list_sessions\n62: \n63: ```python\n64: async def list_sessions(\n65:     self,\n66:     workspace_id: Optional[str] = None,\n67:     limit: int = 100,\n68:     offset: int = 0\n69: ) -> List[Session]\n70: ```\n71: \n72: **Parameters:**\n73: - `workspace_id`: Optional workspace ID to filter by\n74: - `limit`: Maximum number of sessions to return (default: 100)\n75: - `offset`: Pagination offset (default: 0)\n76: \n77: **Returns:** List of `Session` objects\n78: \n79: **Raises:** `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n80: \n81: ##### delete_session\n82: \n83: ```python\n84: async def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> None\n85: ```\n86: \n87: **Parameters:**\n88: - `session_id`: ID of the session\n89: \n90: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n91: \n92: #### Code Execution Methods\n93: \n94: ##### execute_code\n95: \n96: ```python\n97: async def execute_code(\n98:     self,\n99:     session_id: str,\n100:     code: str,\n101:     timeout: Optional[int] = None\n102: ) -> ExecutionResult\n103: ```\n104: \n105: **Parameters:**\n106: - `session_id`: ID of the session\n107: - `code`: Python code to execute\n108: - `timeout`: Optional execution timeout in seconds\n109: \n110: **Returns:** `ExecutionResult` object\n111: \n112: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `ExecutionError`, `TimeoutError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n113: \n114: ##### execute_code_async\n115: \n116: ```python\n117: async def execute_code_async(\n118:     self,\n119:     session_id: str,\n120:     code: str,\n121:     timeout: Optional[int] = None\n122: ) -> ExecutionJob\n123: ```\n124: \n125: **Parameters:**\n126: - `session_id`: ID of the session\n127: - `code`: Python code to execute\n128: - `timeout`: Optional execution timeout in seconds\n129: \n130: **Returns:** `ExecutionJob` object\n131: \n132: **Raises:** `SessionNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n133: \n134: ##### get_execution_result\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: async def get_execution_result(self, job_id: str) -> ExecutionResult\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Parameters:**\n141: - `job_id`: ID of the execution job\n142: \n143: **Returns:** `ExecutionResult` object\n144: \n145: **Raises:** `JobNotFoundError`, `AuthenticationError`, `ConnectionError`\n146: \n147: ## Data Models\n148: \n149: ### Session\n150: \n151: ```python\n152: class Session(BaseModel):\n153:     session_id: str\n154:     workspace_id: str\n155:     status: SessionStatus  # Enum: CREATING, ACTIVE, TERMINATED, ERROR\n156:     created_at: datetime\n157:     updated_at: datetime\n158:     timeout: int\n159:     metadata: Dict[str, str]\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### SessionStatus\n163: \n164: ```python\n165: class SessionStatus(str, Enum):\n166:     CREATING = \"creating\"\n167:     ACTIVE = \"active\"\n168:     TERMINATED = \"terminated\"\n169:     ERROR = \"error\"\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### ExecutionResult\n173: \n174: ```python\n175: class ExecutionResult(BaseModel):\n176:     job_id: str\n177:     session_id: str\n178:     status: ExecutionStatus  # Enum: PENDING, RUNNING, COMPLETED, FAILED\n179:     output: str\n180:     error: Optional[str]\n181:     execution_time: float\n182:     created_at: datetime\n183:     completed_at: Optional[datetime]\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### ExecutionStatus\n187: \n188: ```python\n189: class ExecutionStatus(str, Enum):\n190:     PENDING = \"pending\"\n191:     RUNNING = \"running\"\n192:     COMPLETED = \"completed\"\n193:     FAILED = \"failed\"\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ### ExecutionJob\n197: \n198: ```python\n199: class ExecutionJob(BaseModel):\n200:     job_id: str\n201:     session_id: str\n202:     status: ExecutionStatus\n203:     created_at: datetime\n204: ```\n205: \n206: ## Exception Hierarchy\n207: \n208: ```\n209: CodeInterpreterException\n210: ├── AuthenticationError\n211: ├── ConnectionError\n212: ├── SessionError\n213: │   ├── SessionCreationError\n214: │   └── SessionNotFoundError\n215: ├── ExecutionError\n216: │   ├── JobNotFoundError\n217: │   └── TimeoutError\n218: └── ValidationError\n219: ```\n220: \n221: ## HTTP Endpoints\n222: \n223: ### Session Endpoints\n224: \n225: - `POST /v1/sessions` - Create session\n226: - `GET /v1/sessions/{session_id}` - Get session\n227: - `GET /v1/sessions` - List sessions\n228: - `DELETE /v1/sessions/{session_id}` - Delete session\n229: \n230: ### Execution Endpoints\n231: \n232: - `POST /v1/sessions/{session_id}/execute` - Execute code\n233: - `GET /v1/jobs/{job_id}` - Get execution result\n\n(End of file - total 233 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Specification\n\n## Module: sdk-python\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient Class\n\n#### Constructor\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str,\n        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 30,\n        max_retries: int = 3\n    ) -> None\n```\n\n**Parameters:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/spec.md","time":{"start":1775876614783,"end":1775876614797}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876614800,"sessionID":"ses_28581a9eeffeMoSglUwrTN7FTL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7eaa6a0017grapn4t1p5GuD","messageID":"msg_d7a7e98c4001Zd3WZZMVqL1XBW","sessionID":"ses_28581a9eeffeMoSglUwrTN7FTL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c9f00ed61450431fa20b66b842b46c29","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The CodeInterpreterClient is a Python SDK that provides a high-level interface for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service. It abstracts the underlying HTTP communication and provides a clean, type-safe API for managing code execution sessions.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: 1. **CodeInterpreterClient**: Main client class for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service\n12: 2. **Session Manager**: Manages CodeInterpreter session lifecycle\n13: 3. **Execution Manager**: Handles code execution requests\n14: 4. **Result Processor**: Processes and validates execution results\n15: \n16: ### Key Features\n17: \n18: - Session creation, retrieval, and termination\n19: - Code execution with synchronous and asynchronous modes\n20: - Result streaming and batch retrieval\n21: - Error handling and retry logic\n22: - Type-safe request/response models\n23: \n24: ## API Design\n25: \n26: ### Client Initialization\n27: \n28: ```python\n29: from agentcube.sdk import CodeInterpreterClient\n30: \n31: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n32:     base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n33:     api_key=\"your-api-key\"\n34: )\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Session Management\n38: \n39: ```python\n40: # Create session\n41: session = client.create_session(\n42:     workspace_id=\"workspace-123\",\n43:     timeout=300\n44: )\n45: \n46: # Get session\n47: session = client.get_session(session_id=\"session-123\")\n48: \n49: # List sessions\n50: sessions = client.list_sessions(workspace_id=\"workspace-123\")\n51: \n52: # Delete session\n53: client.delete_session(session_id=\"session-123\")\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Code Execution\n57: \n58: ```python\n59: # Execute code synchronously\n60: result = client.execute_code(\n61:     session_id=\"session-123\",\n62:     code=\"print('Hello, World!')\"\n63: )\n64: \n65: # Execute code asynchronously\n66: job = client.execute_code_async(\n67:     session_id=\"session-123\",\n68:     code=\"x = 1 + 1\"\n69: )\n70: \n71: # Get execution result\n72: result = client.get_execution_result(job_id=\"job-123\")\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ## Data Models\n76: \n77: ### Session\n78: \n79: ```python\n80: class Session(BaseModel):\n81:     session_id: str\n82:     workspace_id: str\n83:     status: SessionStatus\n84:     created_at: datetime\n85:     updated_at: datetime\n86:     timeout: int\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### ExecutionResult\n90: \n91: ```python\n92: class ExecutionResult(BaseModel):\n93:     job_id: str\n94:     session_id: str\n95:     status: ExecutionStatus\n96:     output: str\n97:     error: Optional[str]\n98:     execution_time: float\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ## Error Handling\n102: \n103: - Custom exception types for different error scenarios\n104: - Automatic retry logic for transient errors\n105: - Detailed error messages with context\n106: \n107: ## Testing Strategy\n108: \n109: - Unit tests for client methods\n110: - Integration tests with mock CodeInterpreter service\n111: - End-to-end tests with real service (when available)\n112: \n113: ## Dependencies\n114: \n115: - httpx ^0.24.0 (HTTP client)\n116: - pydantic ^2.0.0 (data validation)\n117: - typing-extensions ^4.0.0 (type hints)\n118: \n119: ## Future Enhancements\n120: \n121: - WebSocket support for streaming output\n122: - Session persistence and recovery\n123: - Advanced debugging features\n124: - Custom execution environment configuration\n\n(End of file - total 124 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThe CodeInterpreterClient is a Python SDK that provides a high-level interface for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service. It abstracts the underlying HTTP communication and provides a clean, type-safe API for managing code execution sessions.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **CodeInterpreterClient**: Main client class for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service\n2. **Session Manager**: Manages CodeInterpreter session lifecycle\n3. **Execution Manager**: Handles code execution requests\n4. **Result Processor**: Processes and validates execution results\n\n### Key Features\n\n- Session creation, retrieval, and termination\n- Code execution with synchronous and asynchronous modes\n- Result streaming and batch retrieval","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","time":{"start":1775876614786,"end":1775876614799}}}}
